# Nitrogen UI Style Guide

Follow the complete style guide in `STYLEGUIDE.md`. Key rules:

## Design Principles

- **White-first surfaces**: Use `#FFFFFF` as default background
- **Restrained color**: Accent colors for borders/focus only, not large fills
- **Typography hierarchy**: Use scale and weight, not color for hierarchy
- **Minimal depth**: Prefer strokes over shadows

## Color Tokens (Always use these exact values)

### Core Surfaces
- `BackgroundPrimary`: `#FFFFFF` (default canvas)
- `BackgroundTinted`: `#EFEAE2` (sparingly, for grouping)
- `SurfacePrimary`: `#FFFFFF` (cards/panels)
- `SurfaceSubtle`: `#F7F7F8` (forms, secondary panels)

### Text
- `TextPrimary`: `#1C1C1E` (primary text)
- `TextSecondary`: `#5A5A60` (metadata)
- `TextTertiary`: `#7A7A82` (helper text)

### Accent (use sparingly)
- `AccentPrimary`: `#8285B6` (borders, focus, selection, links)
- `AccentTint`: `#B2B4D6` (hover backgrounds)
- `AccentWash`: `#E6E7F2` (selected rows)

### Semantic Indicators (meaning, not decoration)
- `IndicatorOrange`: `#B97A5D` (warning/needs review)
- `IndicatorYellow`: `#C6B875` (pending/in progress)
- `IndicatorGreen`: `#9DAA9B` (success/verified)

### Strokes
- `Divider`: `#E6E6EA`
- `StrokeSubtle`: `#E1E1E6` (borders)
- `StrokeAccent`: `#8285B6` (focus borders)

## Typography

- **Primary font**: Inter (body, labels, controls, most headers)
- **Display font**: Urbanist (select hero headers only, 1-2 levels max)
- **Don't mix** Inter + Urbanist in dense tables/forms

## Component Patterns

### ✅ DO
```tsx
// White backgrounds with subtle borders
<div className="bg-white border border-stroke-subtle rounded-lg">

// Semantic indicators as small badges
<span className="bg-indicator-green/10 text-indicator-green">Verified</span>

// Accent for focus/selection
<button className="focus:border-accent-primary focus:ring-accent-wash">
```

### ❌ DON'T
```tsx
// Large accent fills
<div className="bg-accent-primary"> // Too much color

// Multiple accent colors without semantic meaning
<div className="border-blue-500"> // Use defined tokens

// Semantic colors as decoration
<div className="bg-indicator-orange"> // Only for status
```

## Icons

- **Icon System**: Lucide React only (monochromatic SVG icons)
- **Never use emojis** in production UI
- **Icon sizes**: 16px (w-4 h-4) to 24px (w-6 h-6) standard
- **Icon colors**: Inherit from context or use system colors
  - Default: `text-text-secondary`
  - Active/accent: `text-accent`
  - Status: `text-indicator-green/orange/yellow`

```tsx
// ✅ DO
<FileText className="w-5 h-5 text-accent" />
<CheckCircle className="w-4 h-4 text-indicator-green" />

// ❌ DON'T
<span>📄</span> // No emojis
<Icon style={{ color: '#custom' }} /> // Use system colors
```

## Quick Checklist
- [ ] Using white (`#FFFFFF`) as primary background?
- [ ] Accent color only for borders/focus, not large fills?
- [ ] Semantic colors (orange/yellow/green) only for status indicators?
- [ ] Using Inter font by default?
- [ ] Strokes preferred over shadows for separation?
- [ ] Using Lucide React icons (no emojis)?
